Package: occupationCoding
Type: Package
Title: Supervised Learning for Occupation Coding
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Malte Schierholz <malte.schierholz@iab.de>
Maintainer: Malte Schierholz <malte.schierholz@iab.de>
Description: Occupation Coding refers to coding short verbal texts (survey answers)
    into an occupational classification. This package implements several supervised learning
    techniques to simplify its automation. More details can be found in an upcoming publication.
    See predict-functions for some examples of what this package can do.
Depends: R (>= 3.5.0)
License: GPL-3
RoxygenNote: 7.1.1
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
IMPORTS:
    text2vec (== 0.4.0),
    tm (== 0.6-2),
    stringr,
    ggplot2,
    data.table
SUGGESTS:
    glmnet,
    xgboost,
    SnowballC,
    mvtnorm,
    stringdist,
    Matrix,
    parallel,
    readxl
